.TH "snd_pcm_add_chmap_ctls" 9 "snd_pcm_add_chmap_ctls" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_add_chmap_ctls \- create channel-mapping control elements
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_add_chmap_ctls
.BI "(struct snd_pcm *pcm "  ","
.BI "int stream "  ","
.BI "const struct snd_pcm_chmap_elem *chmap "  ","
.BI "int max_channels "  ","
.BI "unsigned long private_value "  ","
.BI "struct snd_pcm_chmap **info_ret "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pcm" 12
the assigned PCM instance
.IP "stream" 12
stream direction
.IP "chmap" 12
channel map elements (for query)
.IP "max_channels" 12
the max number of channels for the stream
.IP "private_value" 12
the value passed to each kcontrol's private_value field
.IP "info_ret" 12
store struct snd_pcm_chmap instance if non-NULL
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create channel-mapping control elements assigned to the given PCM stream(s).
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, or a negative error value.
